            "value": "If a user submits an array instead of an expected string for \"non-array\" form fields, this warning is generated.\r\n\r\nSimple test:\r\n\r\n$form->setMethod('get');\r\n$q = new Zend_Form_Element_Text('q');\r\n$form->addElement($q);\r\n\r\nSubmit the form.  Edit the address bar to be 'q[]=' instead of 'q=' and the Zend View will emit the warning.\r\n"
